't%20have%20a%20plan%20for%20my%20name%2C%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20were%20friends%20long%20before%20we%20were%20anything%20else.%20We're%20casual%20people%2C%20and%20neither%20of%20us%20is%20a%20hopeless%20romantic.%20We%20did%20a%20spur-of-the-moment%20courthouse%20wedding%20that%20felt%20very%20%26quot%3Bus.%26quot%3B%20We%20had%20no%20guests%20(aside%20from%20two%20friends%20as%20witnesses)%2C%20and%20no%20photographer%20(aside%20from%20the%20aforementioned%20friends'%20phone%20camera%20photos).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeading%20up%20to%20the%20big%20day%2C%20we%20tried%20on%20the%20typical%20nomenclature%20for%20size%2C%20mainly%20because%20I%20thought%20that%20was%20what%20you%20were%20supposed%20to%20do.%20My%20options%20were%20to%20become%20Kirby%20Man%2C%20hyphenate%20%C3%A0%20la%20Man-Kelly%20or%20Kelly-Man%2C%20or%20have%20him%20take%20my%20last%20name.%20It's%20not%20that%20I%20disliked%20any%20of%20these%20names%3B%20rather%2C%20it%20felt%20more%20compelling%20to%20exist%20as%20I%20always%20had.%20Why%20would%20I%20change%20my%20identity%20when%20the%20only%20thing%20changing%20was%20my%20marital%20status%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20reason%2C%20keeping%20your%20own%20last%20name%20still%20feels%20a%20bit%20unconventional%2C%20but%20it%20seems%20to%20fit%20the%20rest%20of%20my%20life%20choices%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20a%20married%20woman%2C%20I%20still%20find%20it%20shocking%20when%20one%20of%20my%20peers%20changes%20their%20first-and-last-name%20Instagram%20handle%20to%20that%20of%20their%20husband's.%20Maybe%20it's%20my%20casual%20attitude%20about%20marriage%2C%20or%20I%20still%20feel%20younger%20than%20I%20am%20(newly%2030)%2C%20but%20I%20just%20can't%20wrap%20my%20head%20around%20it.%20Marriage%20is%20an%20equal%20partnership%2C%20and%20the%20idea%20that%20it%20should%20require%20a%20%26quot%3Bgiving%20up%26quot%3B%20of%20something%2C%20even%20willfully%2C%20feels%20suffocating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20thankful%20I%20don