th.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFormidable%20Shield%20is%20Europe's%20largest%20live-fire%20naval%20exercise%20and%20a%20key%20opportunity%20for%20allies%20to%20train%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20air%20defense%20scenarios.%20For%20the%20Thomas%20Hunder%2C%20the%20drills%20included%20missile%20and%20drone%20engagements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223719%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Arleigh%20Burke%20class%20guided-missile%20destroyer%20USS%20Thomas%20Hudner%20(DDG%20116)%20participates%20in%20exercise%20At-Sea%20Demonstration%20(ASD)%20%2F%20Formidable%20Shield%20(FS)%202025.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68417d5d9d73a0031e8de9dd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222479%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUSS%20Thomas%20Hudner%20during%20Formidable%20Shield%20last%20month.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%20photo%20by%20Mass%20Communication%20Specialist%202nd%20Class%20Jonathan%20Nye%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%2C%20toward%20the%20end%20of%20the%20exercise%2C%20a%20handful%20of%20NATO%20warships%20lined%20up%20to%20face%20off%20against%20different%20defense%20scenarios.%20Diaz%20was%20on%20watch%20with%20the%20.50%20caliber%2C%20looking%20out%20over%20the%20water%20and%20waiting%20for%20instructions%20to%20come%20through%20on%20the%20radio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDiaz%20said%20that%20his%20first%20engagement%20that%20day%20was%20a%20remote-controlled%20boat%2C%20simulating%20an%20uncrewed%20surface%20vessel.%20It%20was%20pretty%20far%20out%2C%20and%20he%20could%20barely%20see%20it.%20Thomas%20Hunder%20engaged%20with%20all%20its%20weapons%20systems%3A%20the%20large%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnato-warships-red-sea-prove-deck-guns-fight-drone-war-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efive-inch%20deck%20gun%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Mark%2038%20machine%20gun%20system%2C%20and%20the%20.50%20caliber.%20Eventually%2C%20the%20five-inch%20gun%20hit%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20later%20that%20day%20that%20he%20fought%20the%20flying%20drone%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-military-isnt-ready-drones-potential-biggest-threat-next-battlefield-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esmall%20quadcopter%20system%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Other%20warships%20called%20in%20the%20threat%20to%20Thomas%20Hunder.%20Diaz%20recalled%20that%20he%20couldn't%20see%20it%20at%20first%2C%20but%20eventually%2C%20the%20team%20spotted%20the%20threat%20and%20marked%20it%20as%20a%20contact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drone%20started%20to%20get%20closer%2C%20at%20one%20point%20200%20meters%20(650%20feet)%20out%2C%20getting%20well%20within%20range%20of%20the%20.50%20caliber.%20Diaz%20asked%20for%20permission%20from%20a%20superior%20to%20engage%20the%20drone%20before%20opening%20fire%20alongside%20another%20sailor%20operating%20a%20second%20M2%20Browning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20both%20shooting%2C%26quot%3B%20Diaz%20said.%20%26quot%3BBoom%2C%20boom%2C%20boom%2C%20boom%2C%20boom.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Navy%20Counselor%201st%20Class%20Robert%20Carlos%20fires%20an%20M1A2%20.50%20caliber%20machine%20gun%20amidships%20of%20the%20Arleigh%20Burke-class%20guided-missile%20destroyer%20USS%20Ralph%20Johnson%20(DDG%20114)%20while%20underway%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%2C%20March%2027.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68417dd19d73a0031e8de9e4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBeyond%20the%20.50%20caliber%2C%20Arleigh%20Burke-class%20destroyers%20are%20also%20armed%20with%20bigger%20guns%20and%20missiles.%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%20photo%20by%20Mass%20Communication%20Specialist%201st%20Class%20Hannah%20Fry%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20point%2C%20the%20other%20sailor%20paused%20to%20reload.%20That's%20when%20Diaz%20made%20the%20kill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20I%20shot%20the%20wing%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20Diaz%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20it%20does%20is%2C%20it's%20flying%2C%20and%20it's%20just%20sitting%20there%2C%20and%20it%20just%20%E2%80%94%20donk!%26quot%3B%20he%20explained.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20little%20sway%2C%20and%20it's%20straight%20into%20the%20water.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrones%20of%20this%20size%2C%20often%20just%20a%20few%20inches%20or%20a%20foot%20in%20length%2C%20are%20incredibly%20difficult%20to%20shoot%20down%20because%20they're%20so%20small%20and%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-troops-shoot-balloons-learn-to-defeat-dangerous-drone-threat-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emove%20erratically%20in%20the%20air%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Diaz%20said%20he%20was%20nervous%20during%20the%20engagement%2C%20but%20the%20successful%20hit%20got%20the%20crew%20fired%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECdr.%20Cameron%20Ingram%2C%20Thomas%20Hunder's%20commanding%20officer%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20some%20of%20the%20crewmembers%20were%20watching%20Diaz%20from%20the%20bridge%20wing%20at%20the%20time%2C%20wondering%20whether%20he%20would%20be%20able%20to%20take%20down%20the%20drone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20he%20clips%20it%2C%20and%20it%20falls%2C%26quot%3B%20Ingram%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20whole%20bridge%20wing%20explodes%20with%20excitement%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20sailor%20%26quot%3Bwalks%20a%20step%20taller%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20exercise%20underscores%20how%20the%20US%20Navy%20is%20increasingly%20integrating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-warships-defeated-drones-without-shooting-changing-how-they-fight-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecounter-drone%3C%2Fa%3E%20training%20into%20its%20planning%20as%20it%20absorbs%20lessons%20from%20the%20Red%20Sea%20conflict%2C%20during%20which%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhouthis-getting-smarter-red-sea-attacks-ships-paying-the-price-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EIran-backed%20Houthis%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20Yemen%20regularly%20launched%20drones%20and%20missiles%20at%20military%20and%20civilian%20vessels%20operating%20in%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224782%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Shmavik%20multirotor%20UAV%2C%20a%20Ukrainian%20analog%20of%20the%20Chinese%20DJI%20Mavic%20quadcopter%20popular%20among%20the%20military%2C%20flies%20during%20the%20presentation%20organized%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Strategic%20Industries%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20Kyiv%20region%2C%20north-central%20Ukraine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68417e7d9d73a0031e8de9ee%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223312%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EQuadcopter%20drones%20have%20run%20rampant%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20used%20on%20both%20sides%20for%20surveillance%20and%20strike%20missions.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20by%20Ukrinform%2FUkrinform%2FSipa%20USA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Houthis%20relied%20heavily%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhouthis-hit-israel-attack-drone-upgraded-longer-range-strikes-idf-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eone-way%20attack%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20the%20KAS-04%2C%20or%20Sammad.%20This%20fixed-wing%20drone%2C%20which%20is%20packed%20with%20explosives%20and%20can%20fly%20long%20distances%2C%20is%20much%20larger%20than%20a%20cheap%2C%20commercially%20available%20quadcopter%20drone%20but%20significantly%20smaller%20than%20a%20US%20military%20MQ-9%20Reaper%2C%20a%20well-known%20combat%20drone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20warships%2C%20including%20Thomas%20Hunder%2C%20shot%20down%20Houthi%20KAS-04s.%20The%20ships%20weren't%20known%20to%20have%20battled%20any%20Houthi%20quadcopters%3B%20these%20threats%2C%20however%2C%20are%20something%20the%20Navy%20is%20training%20for%2C%20especially%20considering%20their%20proliferation%20in%20other%20fights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20BI's%20visit%20to%20the%20Thomas%20Hudner%2C%20which%20sailed%20from%20England%20to%20France%20last%20weekend%20ahead%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-dangerous-jobs-american-troops-carried-out-on-d-day-2019-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ED-Day%3C%2Fa%3E%20events%20this%20week%2C%20the%20watch%20team%20spotted%20a%20quadcopter%20drone%20as%20the%20destroyer%20was%20setting%20off%20on%20its%20journey.%20They%20closely%20monitored%20the%20drone%2C%20which%20turned%20out%20not%20to%20pose%20any%20immediate%20danger%20to%20the%20ship.%20Still%2C%20the%20crew%20was%20ready%20to%20take%20action%20if%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIngram%20said%20that%20small%20quadcopters%20are%20%26quot%3Babsolutely%20a%20threat%2C%26quot%3B%20even%20if%20there%20are%20limitations%20in%20their%20capability%2C%20specifically%20endurance%2C%20range%2C%20and%20payload%20capacity.%20While%20these%20drones%20generally%20can't%20carry%20enough%20ordnance%20to%20effectively%20disable%20a%20destroyer%2C%20they%20could%20certainly%20hurt%20people%20and%20do%20enough%20damage%20to%20potentially%20force%20the%20warship%20into%20repairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20there%20will%20probably%20be%20a%20desire%20to%20weaponize%20those%20things%2C%20but%20there%20are%20limitations%2C%26quot%3B%20Ingram%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDestroyers%20like%20his%20don't%20operate%20close%20to%20the%20coast.%20An%20enemy%20would%20have%20to%20send%20the%20drones%20out%20several%20miles%20from%20the%20shore%20or%20have%20a%20launching%20platform%20closer%20to%20the%20warship.%20But%20even%20then%2C%20the%20payload%20wouldn't%20be%20as%20heavy%20as%20a%20Houthi%20KAS-04.%20It%20is%20possible%20that%20the%20ship%20could%20encounter%20one%20near%20port.%20Warships%20have%20been%20attacked%20pierside%20in%20the%20past%2C%20though%20by%20other%20threats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Ukraine%20war%20has%20demonstrated%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-drone-defense-tech-industry-warfare-russia-attacks-2025-4%5C%2